Bollywood star Priyanka Chopra and US singer Nick Jonas are marrying in a Hindu ceremony, a day after exchanging vows according to Christian tradition. The couple are celebrating their nuptials with friends and family at the lavish Umaid Bhavan Palace in the Rajasthani city of Jodhpur. Jonas and Chopra got engaged in the summer after a whirlwind romance. On social media, they said their wedding was an “amalgamation” of their families, faiths and culture. They shared pictures of the ceremony, in which Chopra had her hands and feet decorated with henna by the women of both families. ‘Will you put your property in your spouse’s name?’ trends on Google Stakeholders advocate qualitative education for African children, others Stakeholders advocate qualitative education for African children, others